00:16:29,580 --> 00:16:31,110
what's your kind of dream,jenny?

258
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:32,520
Gettin' out of this town.

259
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:33,250
Goin' where?

260
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:34,210
Anywhere.

261
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:37,160
It's a nice place-  anywhere.I've been there myself many times.

262
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:39,480
It's got to be better than secretarial school.

263
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,310
That so bad?

264
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,390
It's a train ride to squaresville.

265
00:16:45,180 --> 00:16:46,920
see,I wt to be a singer.

266
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:49,620
Get in line. That's a hard dream.

267
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:52,420
But it's mine.People in line aren't my problem.

268
00:16:52,430 --> 00:16:54,010
You sure are feisty,jenny.

269
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:55,220
Born that way.

270
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,480
what the hell you doing with gramps?

271
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:01,950
None of your business,skiz.

272
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:02,780
We're going now.

273
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:03,660
Get off of me!

274
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:05,940
Why don't you take a walk? Cool off.

275
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:10,800
Why don't you keep your nose out of it,old man,before I break it for you?

276
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:14,150
Kid,you rode in here on a bicycle.

277
00:17:14,990 --> 00:17:16,600
I'm quaking in my boots.

278
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:23,480
I'm staying,skiz,so scat.

279
00:17:23,650 --> 00:17:24,870
Woot de do.

280
00:17:38,230 --> 00:17:40,820
This skiz clown-- know his real name?

281
00:17:40,830 --> 00:17:42,340
Scott sienkovic.

282
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:47,180
I remember because he made the front page of the papers a few months later.

283
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:48,890
Boy scout of the year?

284
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:51,490
Armed robbery.

285
00:17:52,020 --> 00:17:53,510
Shot a bank teller.

286
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:01,410
Had it out for hawkins big time,skiz.

287
00:18:02,770 --> 00:18:04,400
And we know you're not shy with a firearm.

288
00:18:04,410 --> 00:18:07,280
Grown man going after a girl half his age.

289
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:09,130
Guy deserved to get shot.

290
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:11,690
You want to tell us where you were the night he died?

291
00:18:11,910 --> 00:18:16,970
Bowling at the thunderbird lanes.Me and 100 other kids heard that needle skip.

292
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:18,900
we'll check that out,skiz.

293
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:20,410
Woot de do.

294
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:23,630
This jenny-- she your girlfriend long?

295
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:27,280
Couple of months,before she got all obsessed with hawkins.

296
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:28,250
How obsessed?

297
00:18:28,260 --> 00:18:30,060
She kept calling the radio,

298
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:31,200
writing him letters,

299
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:32,770
talking about him nonstop.

300
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:34,430
You know,real psycho stuff.

301
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,680
You think they had an affair?

302
00:18:35,690 --> 00:18:37,180
Must have.

303
00:18:37,190 --> 00:18:40,790
Why else would she give two pennies about that loser?

304
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,730
Sounds like it was a one-way street.

305
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:45,510
She got crazier and crazier over it.

306
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:48,870
One night we were in front of a real rock star,

307
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:51,900
and as usual,all she cared about was the hawk.

308
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:57,120
All right! Now here's the one you've been waiting for--

309
00:18:57,330 --> 00:19:00,150
little richard!

310
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:22,370
skiz,you got to help me get to the hawk.

311
00:19:22,380 --> 00:19:23,500
Stop acting nutso,jenny.

312
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:25,160
I got to see him. You don't understand!

313
00:19:25,170 --> 00:19:26,330
He's an old coot. Why do you care?

314
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:28,330
Don't talk about him like that!

315
00:19:28,660 --> 00:19:30,770
You're on your own,dollface.

316
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:36,130
do this,we'll go park later.

317
00:19:37,650 --> 00:19:38,530
Promise?

318
00:19:38,540 --> 00:19:40,440
You helping me get to him or not?

319
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:41,820
Woot de do.

320
00:19:49,330 --> 00:19:50,620
We got to talk to the hawk.

321
00:19:51,110 --> 00:19:52,870
Yeah,and I got a date with jayne mansfield.

322
00:19:52,890 --> 00:19:53,670
You think you're funny?

323
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:54,480
Hawk!

324
00:19:58,370 --> 00:20:00,750
hey! Why'd you stop taking my calls?

325
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:01,730
I've been busy,jenny.

326
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:03,340
You shouldn't even be back here,all right? 

327
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:04,830
I just...I just want to talk.

328
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:06,760
About what?

329
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:07,690
Us.

330
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:08,750
Us?

331
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:11,400
Jenny,there is no us.

332
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,680
I made it for you.

333
00:20:22,770 --> 00:20:25,910
play it. You'll understand everything.

334
00:20:29,430 --> 00:20:31,050
I'll never forget you.

335
00:20:39,490 --> 00:20:40,670
"Scarlet rose."

336
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:44,090
Same song hawk was playing on the radio when he was killed.

337
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:46,600
Know where we can find this jenny?

338
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:49,820
Ran into her after I got out of jail.

339
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,840
All married.Mrs. Jenny monahan.

340
00:20:52,850 --> 00:20:55,350
Pretended like she didn't know me.

341
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:57,280
That's a surprise.

342
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,680
Can I get out of here?

343
00:20:59,690 --> 00:21:00,950
Yeah.

344
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:06,310
Sounds like we got a groupie gone wild.

345
00:21:06,970 --> 00:21:09,840
At 17,you think your first love's your last.

346
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:12,610
Yeah. Every fan knew where the hawk broadcast.

347
00:21:12,620 --> 00:21:14,410
I wonder if jenny found her way there.

348
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:16,220
And found the hawk's gun.

349
00:21:30,470 --> 00:21:31,890
what's going on,mike?

350
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,530
What do you mean?

351
00:21:34,820 --> 00:21:35,930
This.

352
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,090
It's got to be be some kind of virus.

353
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,670
Think I can afford to miss work?

354
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,250
The doc says you're okay physically.

355
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:45,720
Oh,he's just pissed I'm late with his bills.

356
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:57,790
da called me again.

357
00:21:58,620 --> 00:22:01,010
Yeah,this coach fitzpatrick thing. 

358
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:07,520
The case is... falling apart.

359
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:14,330
The only guy who agreed to testify is getting scared.

360
00:22:14,940 --> 00:22:17,250
He might go south on the stand.

361
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:21,390
Judge could toss it.

362
00:22:25,330 --> 00:22:27,270
- You sure you don't remember anything?  
- No way.

363
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,900
I ask because...

364
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:33,210
there was this one night you came home from practice.

365
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:35,170
Oh,god,scotty,that was a long time ago.

366
00:22:35,180 --> 00:22:40,550
Yeah,but I remember,'cause... you were pretty messed up.

367
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:43,500
You slept in your clothes. 

368
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:52,680
you okay,mike?

369
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:55,320
I'm fine.

370
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:57,120
Go to sleep.

371
00:22:58,630 --> 00:23:00,620
Something happen at practice?

372
00:23:01,850 --> 00:23:03,050
No.

373
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:07,050
Hey,why are you being so quiet?

374
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:09,130
Just don't go there no more,okay?

375
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:11,100
Don't go near the coach.

376
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:13,550
Why?

377
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:19,960
You want to play guess?

378
00:23:23,460 --> 00:23:24,860
Come on.

379
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:26,550
Guess this song.

380
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:39,110
you got it?

381
00:23:40,450 --> 00:23:43,610
Scotty,I'm too tired,okay?

382
00:23:45,310 --> 00:23:46,590
Okay.

383
00:23:46,970 --> 00:23:48,510
We'll play tomorrow night.

384
00:23:50,340 --> 00:23:52,190
All right. Night,mikey.

385
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:54,790
Night.

386
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:13,190
I don't remember that night.

387
00:24:14,630 --> 00:24:16,010
Well,what about that song?

388
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:18,040
No.

389
00:24:18,970 --> 00:24:20,090
You're sure?

390
00:24:20,140 --> 00:24:21,080
I'm tired,scotty.

391
00:24:21,090 --> 00:24:24,340
That was the only time I ever saw you get so... bummed out.

392
00:24:24,350 --> 00:24:26,270
I mean,you were crying...

393
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:30,350
if I was bawling,it was probably because that weasel jay shortz cheap-shotted me.

394
00:24:32,750 --> 00:24:35,940
Yeah. Probably.

395
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:38,860
We'll talk later,all right? I'm just beat.

396
00:24:43,510 --> 00:24:44,680
Okay.

397
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:55,140
you don't get better soon,I'm going to pound you.

398
00:24:55,150 --> 00:24:57,140
Oh,yeah,that'll be the day.

399
00:25:34,530 --> 00:25:35,460
How about a little music?

400
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:36,700
May I?

401
00:26:22,390 --> 00:26:24,730
interesting lyrics you wrote for the hawk.

402
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:26,190
How'd you get that record?

403
00:26:26,510 --> 00:26:28,520
Bones kept all of hawk's stuff,

404
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:30,980
including the song he was playing when you killed him.

405
00:26:31,170 --> 00:26:33,630
Me? Oh,you're joking,right?

406
00:26:33,660 --> 00:26:36,340
Back then it was called a teenage crush.

407
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:37,930
Now we call it stalking.

408
00:26:37,940 --> 00:26:41,330
I was a lonely,confused kid, not a murderer.

409
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:43,240
Can't just take your word for it,jenny.

410
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:45,740
I was at home that night with my sisters.

411
00:26:46,330 --> 00:26:50,560
Believe me,hawk had bigger problems than a lovesick teenybopper.

412
00:26:50,570 --> 00:26:52,230
What kind of problems we talking?

413
00:26:54,370 --> 00:26:59,370
One night... I snuck into the station to see him.

414
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,920
I got an idea of what he was up against.

415
00:27:01,930 --> 00:27:02,710
Meaning what?

416
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,650
The record companies.

417
00:27:04,910 --> 00:27:06,900
They were always trying to make him take payola.

418
00:27:06,910 --> 00:27:09,870
Hawk doesn't sound like the kind of dj that would take money to play a song.

419
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,260
Well,that didn't stop them from trying.

420
00:27:20,140 --> 00:27:21,150
Thanks,ben.

421
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:22,740
Didn't know you were buying dinner tonight.

422
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:26,820
I sent you a record last week,expected it on the air by now.

423
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:28,710
I'm not for sale.

424
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,270
Everyone's for sale.

425
00:27:31,140 --> 00:27:33,110
Funny,I heard you play one of my groups today.

426
00:27:33,460 --> 00:27:35,180
Hey,I got nothing against your label.

427
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:37,340
Was it that new warner mack tune? That's pretty hot.

428
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:39,430
No,the darts,"square town."

429
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,330
Oh,bones picked that one.

430
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:43,180
I give him a pick each day.

431
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:44,630
And he chose mine.

432
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:53,000
are you saying that bones took money to play a song?

433
00:27:53,010 --> 00:27:55,310
Bones understands the game.

434
00:27:55,890 --> 00:27:57,770
Djs like you are dinosaurs.

435
00:27:58,010 --> 00:27:59,050
That right?

436
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:01,740
We've got the money,the artists,the control.

437
00:28:01,750 --> 00:28:04,960
Radio is just my personal handshake to the buying public.

438
00:28:04,970 --> 00:28:06,590
And if the buying public doesn't want it?

439
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:10,220
One choice of entree you eat, what's on the plate. 

440
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:13,280
You know what?People like you take everything that is real and good

441
00:28:13,290 --> 00:28:15,930
and you turn it into tinsel.

442
00:28:15,940 --> 00:28:17,500
But the worst part...

443
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:22,520
tinsel-man...  is that you don't even know it.

444
00:28:23,070 --> 00:28:25,600
Oh,so you're the big shot celebrity with all the answers,that it?

445
00:28:25,610 --> 00:28:27,300
No,I'm just like the kids.

446
00:28:27,310 --> 00:28:30,000
I'm a fan. I'm a damned fan of the music.

447
00:28:30,010 --> 00:28:33,630
Now,if you will excuse me,I have to sell some toothpaste.

448
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,960
You give my best to bones.

449
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:37,840
That's right! Zip toothpaste!

450
00:28:38,270 --> 00:28:40,050
If you want to keep your smile hip,

451
00:28:40,060 --> 00:28:42,140
you'd better brush with some zip!

452
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:53,340
Gave up the singing career then and there.

453
00:28:53,350 --> 00:28:55,310
Saw how cutthroat it was.

454
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:57,410
That the last time you saw the hawk?

455
00:28:58,240 --> 00:29:00,070
He looked crushed.

456
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:02,160
So the hawk knew bones was on the take.

457
00:29:02,170 --> 00:29:04,930
And maybe hawk was going to do something about it.

458
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:13,280
Your career is over if authorities knew you were taking payola,right,bones?

459
00:29:13,340 --> 00:29:17,320
Fcc was cracking down,lot of people's lives ruined over that.

460
00:29:18,230 --> 00:29:19,480
You can't prove I took money.

461
00:29:19,490 --> 00:29:21,090
We don't care about payola in '58.

462
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:23,490
We care about who killed john hawkins.

463
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:25,640
Hawk confront you on what you did?

464
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:27,470
The same night he found out.

465
00:29:27,650 --> 00:29:28,810
Keep talking.

466
00:29:29,460 --> 00:29:31,350
I never meant to betray him.

467
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:33,780
But you did,bones.

468
00:29:34,410 --> 00:29:35,810
It didn't matter.

469
00:29:36,780 --> 00:29:39,050
Something had already changed in him.

470
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:43,550
If I get my own show,

471
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:46,380
you girls are my first guests.

472
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:55,040
Bones,we got to talk.

473
00:29:55,050 --> 00:29:56,970
Hawk! Have a seat.

474
00:29:57,250 --> 00:30:02,270
This is,uh,this is gigi,and this is lulu.

475
00:30:02,490 --> 00:30:04,190
Gilugilu.

476
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:05,440
You mind,girls?

477
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,330
We need some privacy.

478
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,290
hurry back.

479
00:30:18,330 --> 00:30:19,730
What are you doing here,bones?

480
00:30:19,790 --> 00:30:22,680
Mr. Ockley invited me.This is some shindig,huh?

481
00:30:22,690 --> 00:30:25,630
I got two chicks after me. Can you believe that?

482
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:27,380
They're hookers,bones.

483
00:30:29,090 --> 00:30:30,360
Wh-what?

484
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:34,190
No,lulu's A dance student, and gigi's A...

485
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,160
stripper.

486
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:37,800
I've seen her act,umbrellas.

487
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:40,270
you're fooling.

488
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,920
I know you took money to play that darts song.

489
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:48,660
It was just one song.

490
00:30:48,670 --> 00:30:51,480
That one song means that they've got me over a barrel.

491
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:52,560
I don't understand...

492
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:54,290
I could go to jail...

493
00:30:56,580 --> 00:30:58,270
because of what you did.

494
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:01,840
Mr. Ockley says it's how the game's played.

495
00:31:01,850 --> 00:31:03,980
You know what the game is,bones?

496
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:07,690
It's the music and the fans who love it.

497
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:09,770
And then there's all this.

498
00:31:09,780 --> 00:31:13,630
The dealmakers,the sellouts,the price of your soul.

499
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:16,470
I'm sorry,hawk.

500
00:31:17,350 --> 00:31:18,910
I'm so sorry.

501
00:31:23,070 --> 00:31:24,570
What are you gonna do?

502
00:31:25,170 --> 00:31:26,620
I don't know,maybe leave philly for a while.

503
00:31:26,630 --> 00:31:27,530
What about your show?

504
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:29,060
Aw,to hell with it.

505
00:31:29,690 --> 00:31:31,070
To hell with all of this.

506
00:31:31,860 --> 00:31:34,170
I got something more important in my life now.

507
00:31:35,390 --> 00:31:36,520
Jenny.

508
00:31:38,620 --> 00:31:39,820
but she's just a fan.

509
00:31:39,830 --> 00:31:41,270
No.

510
00:31:42,250 --> 00:31:43,930
She's more than that.

511
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:47,420
Me and her gonna take a little trip out west.

512
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:50,590
Hawk...

513
00:31:53,450 --> 00:31:55,380
I just wanted to be a winner. 

514
00:31:56,900 --> 00:31:58,640
Like you.

515
00:31:59,020 --> 00:32:00,460
You always were,kid.

516
00:32:14,970 --> 00:32:16,840
Steep price. We all paid.

517
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,650
Some more than others.

518
00:32:19,110 --> 00:32:21,980
So jenny and hawk were going away together?

519
00:32:21,990 --> 00:32:23,630
That was the plan.

520
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:27,120
But,the next night, hawk was dead.

521
00:32:29,820 --> 00:32:32,690
Funny how jenny failed to mention her travel plans with hawk.

522
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:34,280
Failed to mention a lot more than that.

523
00:32:34,610 --> 00:32:38,400
Follow me.That documentary dude? He's got nothing on me.

